The paper focuses on developing a learning algorithm for robotics, specifically for damage recovery. This falls under the category of Robotics (cs.RO). The paper also mentions the use of Reinforcement Learning (RL) algorithms, which falls under the categories of Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the use of a dynamics simulator, which falls under the category of Systems and Control (cs.SY). Finally, the paper evaluates the algorithm on a simulated wheeled robot and a real six-legged walking robot, which involves computer vision (cs.CV) for perception and navigation.
